  "prompt": "Is money laundering a legally actionable offense?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a legally actionable offense in virtually all developed countries and many developing countries. This means that it is a crime that can be prosecuted in a court of law, and individuals or entities found guilty can face a variety of penalties, including:\n\n*   **Criminal Charges:** Imprisonment, fines, and a criminal record.\n*   **Civil Penalties:** Monetary penalties, asset forfeiture (seizure of assets involved in the laundering), and restrictions on business activities.\n\nLaws against money laundering are designed to combat financial crime and terrorism by making it difficult for criminals to profit from their illegal activities. They also aim to protect the integrity of the financial system.\n",
